\par\par \b \uc2  IMF-RI row `does not hurt rupiah but blocks upsurge'. \b0\par\par\uc2 652 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 February 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  deputy governor Miranda Goeltom said on Friday that the current standoff between the government and the International Monetary Fund (IMF) had not impacted on the rupiah, but admitted that it had become a factor in blocking the rupiah's upside potential. \par \par \uc2  Miranda said that other factors, including the ongoing political and social unrest, were also affecting the exchange rate of the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  "Until now, we have not seen the rupiah falling drastically, but if we see it from the side of a possible strengthening in the rupiah, which has not materialized, then we can say there's an effect," she told reporters. \par \par \uc2  "But it is not only due to the issue of relations with the IMF, there are also other factors ... There are still too many \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," she added. \par \par \uc2  Miranda said that the social and political factors could further hurt the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah continued its recent fall late on Friday due to a combination of corporate demand for dollars to repay overseas debt and ongoing ethnic clashes in Sampit, Central Kalimantan, which have claimed at least 143 lives. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah ended trading at Rp 9,685 per U.S. dollar from Rp 9,630 late on Thursday. \par \par \uc2  State banks failed to defend the rupiah, dealers said. \par \par \uc2  State banks had sold dollars around Rp 9,660 per dollar in the morning and around Rp 9,665 in the afternoon, Dow Jones newswires quoted dealers as saying. \par \par \uc2  The size of the sale, estimated to be around US$10 million to $20 million, wasn't big enough to counter the dollar's ascent, dealers said. \par \par \uc2  "The selling was well absorbed by the market," said a dealer at a European bank, adding that he expected more weakness in the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  Miranda also reiterated that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's new foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  launched in the middle of last month, which cut off rupiah transfers to offshore banks to help curb speculation against the currency, had helped in reducing the volatility of the rupiah amid the current political turbulence. \par \par \uc2  Relations between the government and the IMF have worsened since last year after the IMF delayed the disbursement of its scheduled $400 million loan tranche to Indonesia due to concerns over the government's proposed amendment of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  law, poorly-designed \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  decentralization policies and delays in the divestment of government ownership in Bank Central Asia (BCA) and Bank Niaga. \par \par \uc2  Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Rizal Ramli traveled to Washington earlier this week to meet with the IMF first deputy managing director Stanley Fischer to lobby the IMF to disburse its funds. \par \par \uc2  Disbursement of the IMF funds is seen as a crucial factor in reviving investor confidence, thus, affecting sentiment in the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  The most difficult issue causing the impasse between the government and the IMF is the government-proposed bill on the amendment of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  law. \par \par \uc2  The IMF has insisted that the amendment process could threaten the independence of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 , but the government has said that the amendment will improve the accountability of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  One of the controversial points in the proposed bill is the requirement for the current board of governors of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  to be automatically dismissed once the new bill has been approved by the legislature, raising concerns over the independence of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Critics have earlier said that the proposed bill is only intended to accommodate President Abdurrahman Wahid's desire to dismiss \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  governor Sjahril Sabirin and his deputies. \par \par \uc2  Another threat to the independence of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  is the proposal to allow the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to resume its function of lending money to the government. Sources say that this point also concerns the IMF. \par \par \uc2  The legislature is expected to resume debate of the new bill soon after Rizal returns from Washington on Monday. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx2o00464\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
