\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia \highlight\uc2  forex ruling hurts local hedging market. \b0\par\par\uc2 595 \uc2 words\par \uc2 2 March 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's ban on offshore forward transactions has eliminated the ability of local companies to protect their dollar borrowings as most local banks are still too weak to offer large hedging transactions, an executive at a state brokerage said on Thursday. \par \par \uc2  Vice president of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  research at state brokerage firm PT Danareksa Sekuritas Raden Pardede said that \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's forex ruling might have even induced the rupiah's recent weakening. \par \par \uc2  "They (\b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) have tried to contain the rupiah's fluctuation with the ruling, but what we've seen lately is that it has fallen sharply nonetheless," Raden told reporters on the sidelines of a seminar on Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  outlook held by Danareksa. \par \par \uc2  On Monday, the rupiah unexpectedly dropped to 9,830 against the U.S dollar from its opening position of 9,685, after weeks of relatively steady performance. \par \par \uc2  Analysts have blamed worsening ethnic clashes in Sampit, Central Kalimantan for the sharp drop. \par \par \uc2  The still \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  prospects of Indonesia's relations with the International Monetary Fund (IMF) has also shed a negative sentiment across the market. \par \par \uc2  But according to Raden, companies have scooped the U.S dollar in the spot market on Monday, as local banks couldn't cope with the surge in hedging demands. \par \par \uc2  "This move has placed a great deal of pressure on the rupiah lately. Security or political worries just add to the pressure," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said companies with U.S dollar denominated debts had feared the rupiah would keep falling, and so they wanted to hedge their dollar positions. \par \par \uc2  But local banks were unable to meet the demand, he said. \par \par \uc2  Raden said that banks here could hardly speculate on the forward market, as they were still in the process of recovery. \par \par \uc2  And since the new ruling abolished the offshore rupiah forward market, he went on, companies were unable to hedge their dollars in Singapore. \par \par \uc2  "The ruling has prevented companies from doing the hedging in Singapore," he explained. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  issued the ruling in January, in an attempt to lower the rupiah's volatility by curbing offshore speculation on the currency. \par \par \uc2  The ruling bans the transfer of rupiah from onshore banks to nonresident parties, thus closing speculators' access to funding for short rupiah positions. \par \par \uc2  It also limits the maximum forward transaction without any underlying investment purposes between onshore banks and nonresidents to US$3 million from $5 million. \par \par \uc2  Analysts have also said the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  has effectively shut down the offshore market in the rupiah, making it difficult for overseas dealers to speculate against the currency since the supply of rupiah funds has virtually dried up. \par \par \uc2  Since the ruling was implemented on Feb. 7, the rupiah gained in stability amidst the then mounting political tension. \par \par \uc2  Reports of a worsening relationship between the government and the IMF failed to hurt the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  Until last week, when ethnic clashes in Sampit broke out, the rupiah maintained its relatively stable course. \par \par \uc2  But Raden said that speculators were needed to allow companies to hedge their dollar positions. \par \par \uc2  "There is a real demand out there for debt repayment in U.S dollars," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said speculators often become \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's scapegoats when blaming the rupiah's fall. \par \par \uc2  Even though the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's ruling cut speculation on the rupiah, he continued, the currency fell sharply anyway. \par \par \uc2  "The ruling has proven to be counterproductive," he said. \par \par \uc2  On Thursday, the rupiah closed at 9,860 against the dollar only slightly lower from its opening at 9,855. (bkm) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx32003bx\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
