\par\par \b \uc2  BI forecast  \highlight22\uc2 economy \highlight\uc2  to grow 4.5-5.5% in 2001. \b0\par\par\uc2 597 \uc2 words\par \uc2 2 March 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  reiterated in its annual report issued on Thursday that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in 2001 was forecast to grow by between 4.5 percent and 5.5 percent. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  said that the growth forecast was based on the assumption of an acceleration in the implementation of the program of key \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms, and improvements in the political and security condition at home. \par \par \uc2  "\b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  believes that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery process in 2001 will gain strength and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth could reach 4.5 percent - 5.5 percent," the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  said. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  grew by 4.8 percent as measured in terms of gross domestic product, last year for the first time, after the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  contracted by nearly 14 percent in 1998, following the devastating \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. \par \par \uc2  Last year's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth was mostly spurred by exports and investments. \par \par \uc2  But with the prospect of slower \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the U.S. (Indonesia's largest export market), and continuing social and political unrest at home which could affect investment, some analysts said that \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth this year would be slower. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  also forecast core inflation to reach between 4 percent and 6 percent this year versus 9.3 percent last year. \par \par \uc2  It said that if the planned increases in government-controlled prices were taken into account, it could contribute another 2 percent - 2.5 percent. \par \par \uc2  The government plans to raise fuel prices by an average of 20 percent this year, possibly in April, and also to raise electricity tariffs in June. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said that to achieve the inflation target, currency in circulation was projected to grow by 11 percent - 12 percent this year. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  also reiterated it would maintain its tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in a bid to achieve the low inflation target. \par \par \uc2  The government earlier called on \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  not to let its benchmark interest rate move too high as it could inhibit \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and threaten the banking sector. \par \par \uc2  Some banks have expressed fears that they could suffer financial bleeding again due to negative spread problems if \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  continue to move higher. \par \par \uc2  The benchmark interest rate of one-month \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  SBI promissory notes moved slightly higher on Wednesday to 14.79 percent, which helped prevent the ailing rupiah fall further against the U.S. dollar. \par \par \uc2  The figures in the annual report had mostly been reported at a press conference earlier in January. \par \par \uc2  Elsewhere, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said that there were at least seven risk factors that could become a threat to its macro-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  target. \par \par \uc2  These include persistent political and security \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  at home, slow progress in corporate debt restructuring, banking intermediary functions which have yet to run normally, continuing legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and the prospect of slower \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the U.S. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  did not mention its target for the exchange rate of the rupiah, but earlier in January it forecast the rupiah to appreciate to between Rp 7,750 - Rp 8,250 per U.S. dollar. \par \par \uc2  The local unit has recently dropped to near the Rp 9,900 level amid ethnic violence in Central Kalimantan which has killed hundreds of people. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah was trading at around Rp 9,860 per dollar late on Thursday compared with Rp 9,855 on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  new forex ruling introduced in the middle of January, which bans the lending of rupiah to non-residents to help speculation against the currency, has helped in reducing the volatility of the local unit. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx32003ce\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
