\par\par \b \uc2  Sjahril, Akbar to discuss reshuffle at  \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 617 \uc2 words\par \uc2 6 March 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) Governor Sjahril Sabirin plans to meet Speaker of the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  Akbar Tandjung on Tuesday (today) to discuss the list of candidates proposed to replace deputy governors Achwan and Dono Iskandar. \par \par \uc2  Sjahril said at the weekend that Achwan and Dono would end their terms on May 17. \par \par \uc2  "It's up to the House to decide," he said. \par \par \uc2  According to the existing \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  law, the deputy governors of BI are selected by the legislature from the list of candidates submitted either by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  governor or deputy governor. \par \par \uc2  Separately, Akbar confirmed on Friday the planned meeting. \par \par \uc2  Akbar said that the candidates proposed to replace Achwan included BI internal finance director Bunbunan Hutapea, director for banking supervision Siti Fadjriah, and Maulana Ibrahim, also an executive of the banking supervision department. \par \par \uc2  He added that the candidates to replace Dono included BI chief representative in New York Taslim Tajudin, BI chief representative in Tokyo Maman Suherman, and director for research on \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Hartadi A. Sarwono. \par \par \uc2  Dono had earlier been appointed to become Indonesia's envoy to the International Monetary Fund (IMF) in Washington. \par \par \uc2  Elsewhere, Akbar said that the House would proceed with the appointment of the two new deputy governors despite the amendment of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  law. \par \par \uc2  The government has proposed a bill to the parliament to amend the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  law. One of the points in the proposed amendment is for the existing BI board of governors to resign once the House approves the bill. \par \par \uc2  The House will resume debating the proposed amendments on March 12, but Akbar said that the deliberation had so far been slow and it was still \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  when it would be completed. \par \par \uc2  The IMF had earlier expressed concern over the proposed amendment as it could threaten the independence of BI. The Fund delayed the disbursement of its third loan tranche to the country late last year partly due to this concern. \par \par \uc2  But the government has insisted that the amendment was needed to boost the accountability of BI. \par \par \uc2  Dono and Achwan are among the five top BI officials who tendered their resignation last November following calls from President Abdurrahman Wahid for BI board members, including Sjahril, to resign as part of efforts to reshuffle and clean up the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  from past corrupt practices. \par \par \uc2  The three other top BI officials who tendered their resignation were senior deputy governor Anwar Nasution, and deputy governors Miranda Goeltom and Burhanuddin Abdullah. \par \par \uc2  But the three remain active until now. \par \par \uc2  The resignation of the top BI officials was made at a time when Sjahril was still under the custody of the Attorney General's Office over alleged involvement in the high profile Bank Bali scandal. \par \par \uc2  Sjahril has denied any wrongdoing and also rejected calls from the President to resign. He is now under trial as a defendant in the Bank Bali scandal. \par \par \uc2  BI had been troubled for more than a year due to a dispute with the government over the controversial emergency liquidity support for ailing domestic banks. \par \par \uc2  The government, via the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , injected some Rp 144.5 trillion in emergency loans into troubled domestic banks between September 1997 and January 1999 to help reimburse depositors' money at a time of massive bank runs. \par \par \uc2  But the Supreme Audit Agency (BPK) revealed in its audit report that some Rp 138 trillion of the liquidity support facilities had been improperly channeled by BI. \par \par \uc2  After months of debate, the government and BI finally agreed last November that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  would pay Rp 24.5 trillion to help cover the losses by issuing bonds to the government. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx36003l9\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  BI - Ceiling of NPLs at 5%. \b0\par\par\uc2 414 \uc2 words\par \uc2 7 March 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  BI Governor Syahril Sabirin has said that banks shall have non-performing loans at no more than 5% by the end of the year. \par \par \uc2  "The ruling is still in force, and is applicable to recapitalized banks," he told Bisnis here yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Syahril said sanctions would be imposed on banks that violate the ruling. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  requires banks to have a CAR of a minimum of 8% and NPLs at 5% by the end of 2001. \par \par \uc2  A senior BI official, JokoSarwono, said, "All banks now have a CAR of \par \par \uc2  above 4%." \par \par \uc2  BI, said Joko, would act tough in seeing that the ruling be adhered to. \par \par \uc2  He noted that Bank BNI once offered a business plan with NPLs at over 5%. \par \par \uc2  "We of course rejected it" \par \par \uc2  However, banks have complained that the target of 5% NPLs by the end of 2001 would be difficult to attain, as the recovery of the real sector \par \par \uc2  requires more time. \par \par \uc2  Bank BNI CEO Saefuddien Hasan said the target is difficult to achieve, as the socio-political situation remains unstable. \par \par \uc2  Earlier, Bank Danamon CEO Arwin Rasyid said bringing down the bank's NPLs from 8,5% to 5% by the end of 2001 faces external constraints. \par \par \uc2  "This includes rising \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the erratic forex rates, as well as legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and poor \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation," he said. \par \par \uc2  Banking analyst Marjanto Danusaputro said for banks not to have NPLs at more than 5%, they should raise their credit disbursement levels. \par \par \uc2  Marjanto gave an example of a bank with credits at Rp100 with an NPL of 20%. \par \par \uc2  He said the NPLs would fall below 20% if the value of credits exceeded \par \par \uc2  Rp100. \par \par \uc2  "The problem is that banks face difficulties in channeling credits. This shows that banks might either be over-cautious or that businessmen have refused to deal with banks anymore," he said. \par \par \uc2  Marjanto noted that banks are seriously working to have a maximum of 5% in NPLs, "but in general they have a problem in reaching that figure." \par \par \uc2  "In the third quarter, one would be able to see which bank has the \par \par \uc2  capability to attain that target." \par \par \uc2  The former BI official pessimism is based on the poor macro condition of the banking and real sectors. \par \par \uc2  "However, some \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  indicators have improved, namely lower inflation and lower imports and higher exports." \par \par \uc2  Marjanto added that BI should act sternly but must also realize that banks have been working hard to reach that figure of 5% in NPLs. (yn). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010710dx37000af\par }\page {\par\fs2