\par\par \b \uc2  Government to set rupiah at 7,800-8,500 in 2002  \highlight22\uc2 budget \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 603 \uc2 words\par \uc2 9 March 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The government will base the 2002 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  on an exchange rate of between Rp 7,800 and Rp 8,500 against the U.S. dollar although the Indonesian currency remains under strong pressure. \par \par \uc2  Finance Minister Prijadi Praptosuhardjo said on Thursday the government was confident that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would allow the rupiah to stabilize at that range. \par \par \uc2  Speaking before the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 ' \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  committee, Prijadi said that the assumption was made in line with efforts to keep the rupiah exchange rate conducive for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "We see an improvement of noneconomic factors in 2002 and this will bring a positive impact on investment activities, consumption, exports and the rupiah exchange rate," he said during the hearing. \par \par \uc2  The current state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which will end in December, is based upon a rupiah-dollar exchange rate of Rp 7,800. \par \par \uc2  But a combination of political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  has sent the rupiah sliding from that target since the fourth quarter of last year. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah has remained in a weak position for months. Analysts estimate that the rupiah could further weaken to below Rp 10,000 against the American greenback. \par \par \uc2  A \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  ruling, which was recently issued to curb speculative attacks on the currency, has only slowed down the rupiah's fall. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah ended Thursday trading at 9,930 against the dollar from 9,880, after Standard & Poor downgraded Indonesia's sovereign debt rating to negative from stable. \par \par \uc2  But Prijadi said in addition to the expected improvement in the political situation, the country's ability to avoid the impact of the slowdown in the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would become an incentive for a stronger rupiah. \par \par \uc2  "The estimated global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown in the year 2002 will have no significant impact on the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he told legislators. \par \par \uc2  But he did not say how Indonesia was going to achieve that, given the country's high dependence on export revenues to fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. \par \par \uc2  The government also plans to set an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth assumption of between 4.5 percent and 5.5 percent in the 2002 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  or within the same range for the current \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The inflation rate target in the next \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  will be set at between 6 percent to 9 percent as compared to 7 percent in the present \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The oil price assumption to calculate state revenues from crude oil exports will be set at between $18 and $22 per barrel as compared to $24 per barrel in the current \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  A sharp increase in export earnings partly due to high oil prices became a dominant factor in the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth during 2000. \par \par \uc2  Crude oil production from state owned oil and gas company Pertamina is estimated at between 1.38 million barrels per day (bpd) to 1.46 million bpd. \par \par \uc2  In 2002, the government will prioritize educational activities, absorbing about 25 percent of the total \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Next comes \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  on agriculture and irrigation which will fork out a 15 percent share of the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Transportation developments are allotted with a 12 percent share, followed by health and welfare \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  with 10 percent. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  on mines and the energy sector is estimated to take up 6.5 percent of the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , while the security sector will probably need 6 percent. \par \par \uc2  The government will issue its preliminary state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumptions so that the House's \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  committee can assess the figures. \par \par \uc2  A draft of the 2002 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which runs from January to December, will be presented in October.(bkm) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx39003yv\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
