ing pessimism toward the government's ability to make the business atmosphere in the country fair and just. \par \par \uc2  Overwhelmed by an \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  future, confidence of CEOs in their ability to foresee the future of their businesses has been falling closer to 100. This has resulted in an increased disinclination to enter new contracts or renew current contracts. \par \par \uc2  "Businessmen are inclined to delay or reduce business \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as they are becoming less confident in their estimations of profitability," it said. \par \par \uc2  Since most of businessmen preferred to keep a larger part of their cash and be free of any commitments for the next six-month period, business \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been on the decline. \par \par \uc2  "Consequently, the business community's market is shrinking," the agency added.(03) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx390040x\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
