\par\par \b \uc2  Government reform target ready for IMF review. \b0\par\par\uc2 750 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 March 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): All \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform targets stated in the latest Letter of Intent (LoI), which has been agreed by the International Monetary Fund (IMF), have basically been completed, according to a senior government official. \par \par \uc2  Assistant to the coordinating minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Dipo Alam said on Friday that he was optimistic that all the reform programs would be ready for the Fund's review before the end of this month. \par \par \uc2  "We're working quickly on the LoI, but I'm afraid I can't name any dates yet," Dipo told reporters after a meeting with the government \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team responsible for the LoI. \par \par \uc2  The LoI contains a set of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform targets that the government agreed to meet as a condition for obtaining loans from the IMF. \par \par \uc2  The IMF has delayed the disbursement of its $400 million loan tranche since December after the government failed to meet the required targets. The loan is part of the Fund's $5 billion loan package to help Indonesia cope with its worst ever \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. \par \par \uc2  Among the uncompleted targets were the divestment of government shares in Bank Central Asia (BCA) and Bank Niaga. \par \par \uc2  Last year, the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  disapproved the divestment plan, due to the then unfavorable market conditions. \par \par \uc2  But since then relations with the IMF have deteriorated and legislators last week approved the plan. The government plans to divest 40 percent of its ownership in BCA, and 51 percent in Bank Niaga sometime in the middle of this year. \par \par \uc2  Dipo said that the government has resolved the divestment issue as demanded under the LoI, although its implementation will take several months. \par \par \uc2  He also dismissed several media reports which claimed that the government was \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  as to how much it planned to divest from the two banks. \par \par \uc2  "We've made sure that we will stick to our agreement with the House," he said. \par \par \uc2  Another reform target, he said, is the issuance of regulations which would govern the creation of a contingency plan to cope with the possible shortfall of the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Dipo said that the government was working on deciding how to manage this contingency \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "We hope to issue a government \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  and an accompanying ministerial decree (for the contingency \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) next week," he said. \par \par \uc2  He added that the IMF additionally requested the government to finalize government regulations regarding the regional financial information system. \par \par \uc2  The regional financial information system is necessary to consolidate the differing financial conditions of each region under the decentralized \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Regions must report their \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  status, and transaction flows to central government in order to update a data base of every region's financial condition. \par \par \uc2  "We're preparing a government \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the regional financial information system, and we expect the President to sign it by next week," he said. \par \par \uc2  Aside from targets outlined in the latest LoI, the IMF asked for the amendment of \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  Law No 23/1999 to be addressed without weakening \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's independence. \par \par \uc2  Dipo said that the government had agreed to the IMF's request for a panel, comprising IMF and government-appointed experts, to provide input on the government-proposed bill. \par \par \uc2  "We've told the IMF that we're ready to form that panel. We're currently discussing with the House on the panel's mechanism," he said. \par \par \uc2  Its formation stemmed from the IMF's concern that the new law would weaken \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's independence, which was a key reform target stipulated in the 1998 LoI. \par \par \uc2  Other concerns were that the move to amend the law was politically motivated, in order to oust \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's current governor Sjahril Sabirin. \par \par \uc2  Sjahril's job is still seen as politically strategic, despite \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's guaranteed independence from government intervention. \par \par \uc2  Legislators have urged that the new \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  law give politicians the opportunity to hold the top position at \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Dipo went on saying that IMF representatives on the panel include a former \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  governor from Chile, and another still active \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  governor from New Zealand. \par \par \uc2  This differs from an earlier government statement which said the representatives were two former \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  governors from Brazil and Canada. \par \par \uc2  According to Dipo, government representatives on the panel would include two banking experts. \par \par \uc2  "All we have to do now is to find these experts," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said that he would meet with the IMF team on Friday evening for further discussions on the LoI. (bkm) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx3a004fu\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
