\par\par \b \uc2  TUESDAY 12th March EDITORIALS OF INDONESIA'S MAJOR DAILIES. \b0\par\par\uc2 844 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 March 2001\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Asia Pulse Pte Limited.< Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its\par \par \uc2  NO TO DEMONSTRATORS \par \par \uc2  Spearheaded by the Federation of the All Indonesian Students Union, massive demonstrations were held yesterday in front of the Merdeka Palace. The rather small mob was protesting against the projected increase in fuel prices, and demanded the resignation of President Andurrahman Wahid. \par \par \uc2  For the umpteenth time President Wahid, in response to the demands of the 'students', stressed that he does not intend to resign and that he has relegated the day-to-day handling of cabinet affairs to Vice President Megawati Soekarnoputri. \par \par \uc2  Sucipto, Secretary General of PDI-P, stated yesterday in an interview that the party wished for Megawati to take over as president and that the whole party would then stand ready to secure Megawati's safety and her position as president. \par \par \uc2  Most people with a certain affinity for Wahid, do not seem to get tired of again proposing the holding of reconciliation talks, but with him remaining as president. However, some supporters who have given him well meant advice, that abandoning the position of president does not mean the end of the world for him. \par \par \uc2  A honorable post can always be created for him, which would make it possible for him to appear at national or other festive functions as elder statesman. This we think is much more honorable and beneficial for the country rather than fomenting hatred against the opposition thereby creating a dangerous situation which may get out of hand. - The Indonesian Observer \par \par \uc2  THE CRISIS DEEPENS \par \par \uc2  The rupiah predictably plunged past 11,000 to the U.S dollar on Monday morning before closing up at 10,700 and dragged down the composite price index of the Jakarta Stock Exchange to 396.611, below psychological level. \par \par \uc2  Amid the festering political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  that seems to have turned into a game of brinkmanship between the \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  Assembly and the President, plus sporadic bouts of civil unrest and stalled negotiations with the International Monetary Fund (IMF), not a single \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  measure appears to matter anymore. \par \par \uc2  With a total foreign debt of US$140 billion, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  which holds only about US$29.1 billion in gross foreign \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 , is certainly impotent to influence the demand-supply equation in the market. \par \par \uc2  Government economist might argue vehemently that the rupiah exchange rate is now grossly undervalued, compared with the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals. But \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals certainly do not count for much when the system of law enforcement and \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  order is breaking down as at present in many parts of the country. \par \par \uc2      It is almost impossible to predict how much further the JSX \par \par \uc2  index could crumble or the rupiah might fall in the coming days. \par \par \uc2      We can only hope that Abdurrahman and the House leaders will \par \par \uc2  immediately stop their bickering, put aside their power ambitions and start acting and working together to save the nation from plunging into an even deeper crisis. -The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2  THE RUPIAH AND THE CALL FOR A STRIKE \par \par \uc2      Yesterday, the rupiah plunged to 11,500 against the US dollar, \par \par \uc2  its lowest level in the past 30 months. \par \par \uc2      The university students' demonstrations calling for a nationwide \par \par \uc2  strike and demanding President Abdurrahman Wahid's resignation had contributed to the drastic drop of the rupiah against the US dollar. \par \par \uc2  The decline in the value of the Indonesian currency has also been triggered by political instability at home despite good indications in Indonesia's macroeconomy. \par \par \uc2  Fortunately, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  yesterday intervened with at least US$ 5 million. However, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) might not continue this measure as it would be a waste of foreign exchange. \par \par \uc2  Efforts to deal with the drop in the rupiah's value against the dollar should be made through political means because the currency fell due to political instability. \par \par \uc2  A \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  which could appease market players is badly needed. The people are awaiting the result of this morning's meeting between BI and the government. - Bisnis Indonesia \par \par \uc2  WATCHING DEMOCRACY \par \par \uc2  Jakarta on Monday turned into an interesting show of democracy which to some people was a sick democracy. Sick because demonstration is considered as mass mobilization. \par \par \uc2  What we saw yesterday was a paradox of democracy and reform. Our leaders could no longer differentiate between personal and institutional sovereignty. \par \par \uc2      It was a mistake for President Abdurrahman Wahid to say that he \par \par \uc2  is not resigning because he still has abundant supporters. \par \par \uc2      It was also a paradox when chairman of the People's Consultative \par \par \uc2  Assembly, Amien Rais, joined the demonstrators. Rais might argue that he was picked up by the students but what was the urgent need for him to be there? \par \par \uc2  Then, the students. They campaigned as a moral force, as if they were naive children who did not want to play political games. But when they called on people to go on a strike to oust Gus Dur, these students had dragged themselves into a political conflict. \par \par \uc2  Our politics has lost its basic elements - ethics and morality. In the absence of rules, people could do anything. That is why democracy and reform always die young in this country. - Media Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010709dx3c000w0\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
