\par\par \b \uc2  Nation in danger of collapse if instability not resolved - Susilo. \b0\par\par\uc2 617 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 March 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Coordinating Minister for Political, Social and Security Affairs Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono warned of the nation's collapse if questions over the national leadership, stability and security are not quickly resolved. \par \par \uc2  Alluding to the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 ' memorandum process against President Abdurrahman Wahid and a possible special session of the People's Consultative Assembly, Susilo believes the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  will last until July or August, bringing with it debilitating consequences. \par \par \uc2  "This \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  will have a severe impact, not only on the political front, but also in our \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2 , social and security fields," he said adding that he was also concerned that it will be aggravated by political activism which will further agitate the conflict. \par \par \uc2  "Quite honestly, with the issuance of a memorandum by the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  against President Abdurrahman Wahid, the credibility and authority of Gus Dur has decreased, which directly or indirectly has effected the credibility of the government," Susilo said. \par \par \uc2  Usually reserved from making direct political statements, Susilo in what seemed to be an expression of his frustration and concern at the state of the nation, on Sunday personally distributed a six-page statement to journalists written on paper that did not include the official masthead of his office. \par \par \uc2  The solution, he said, lies in the hands of this nation's political elite: Abdurrahman, Vice President Megawati Soekarnoputri, Assembly Speaker Amien Rais and House Speaker Akbar Tandjung. \par \par \uc2  He added that the House, the government and major political parties can also influence the solution. \par \par \uc2  In the statement, Susilo then pleaded for an end to the use of violence as a means of resolving the national leadership issue. \par \par \uc2  "The word is peace and order, no matter how large the mass demonstrations are." \par \par \uc2  Susilo then charged that even though the term "national stability and security" may be considered unpopular due to its militaristic connotation, but added that "without it this nation would be a sea of chaos, violence and tension." \par \par \uc2  He called for a common perception among all elements of society to arrive at a consensus which can be pursued. \par \par \uc2  "Don't practice the law of the jungle. Don't implement a principle of winner takes all," Susilo appealed. \par \par \uc2  But elsewhere over the weekend the politicking continued. \par \par \uc2  Golkar Party chairman Akbar Tandjung in Makassar, South Sulawesi, punctuated the growing support for Megawati to succeed the presidency. \par \par \uc2  Speaking to journalists after delivering a political speech in before the party's cadres on Saturday, Akbar said he will provide total support for Megawati if she replaces Abdurrahman in a constitutional manner. \par \par \uc2  "If in a constitutional way Megawati replaces Gus Dur, Golkar will give its support to her to ensure that she will succeed to lead the country as president," Akbar remarked. \par \par \uc2  Support for Megawati to take over from the embattled President has grown following the issuance of a memorandum against Abdurrahman after he was implicated in two financial scandals by the House. \par \par \uc2  Ironically the most ardent pronouncements for Megawati in recent weeks have come from the very same Islamic parties which stifled her presidential bid in 1999 by declaring that it would be improper for a woman to be president. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile in Jakarta, PDI Perjuangan hinted that the party was not merely seeking backing for Megawati, but also assurances that if she takes over she will not endure the kind of political assault as her predecessor. \par \par \uc2  "What we are doing is not simply trying to gain support for Megawati, but also to achieve political stability needed by all political parties for the next general election," secretary of the party's faction at the House, Heri Akhmadi, told The Jakarta Post. (02/27/30/dja) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx3c004a6\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  'Rupiah weakens on panic buying'. \b0\par\par\uc2 342 \uc2 words\par \uc2 13 March 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Financial analyst Theo F. Toemion said recent \par \par \uc2  rupiah depreciation against the US dollar was not a form of market \par \par \uc2  punishment for the government. \par \par \uc2  He said the depreciation had been caused by panic buying on \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  over \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's strategy to salvage the national currency. \par \par \uc2  Theo said the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  should have given explanation on the real \par \par \uc2  reasons for the currency collapse to avoid panic. \par \par \uc2  On top of this, Theo said, the President and Vice President of the country \par \par \uc2  should be seen united and not divided. \par \par \uc2  BI has over the past five months been trying to take rupiah off the \par \par \uc2  political theater. Theo said it should have done this long time ago. \par \par \uc2  Theo said that to follow up on BI's restriction of forward transactions, \par \par \uc2  the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  should begin now to restrict spot market transactions as \par 