\par\par \b \uc2  Govt, House decide to postpone debate on BI law until May. \b0\par\par\uc2 673 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 March 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The government said on Wednesday it would delay until May discussions with the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the amendment of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  law to allow the International Monetary Fund (IMF)-sponsored panel of \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  experts to review the proposed amendments. \par \par \uc2  Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Rizal Ramli said the government and the House agreed in a meeting on Tuesday night to postpone the deliberations on proposed amendments to \b \highlight22\uc2 Central Bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  Law No 23/1999. \par \par \uc2  "We've agreed to defer deliberations, supposed to be resumed early this week, until after the House's recess," Rizal told reporters. \par \par \uc2  The House would take a recess in April, and would resume work in the second week of May, he added. \par \par \uc2  The IMF has asked the government to postpone the deliberations until an independent panel of experts examined the planned amendments, which have been one of the key reasons behind the delay of the disbursement of the latest tranche of the IMF loan since last December. \par \par \uc2  The multilateral agency, which is sponsoring a US$5 billion bailout program for Indonesia, has expressed great concern that hasty amendments of the law might result in stripping away \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's independence, which has been established by Law No.23/1999. \par \par \uc2  The IMF fears that political meddling with the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's monetary policies would jeopardize the macroeconomic management of the country. \par \par \uc2  Many analysts have also criticized the proposed amendments to the law mainly as a ploy on the part of President Abddurrahman Wahid to oust Sjahril Sabirin, the current governor of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Under the current \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  law, neither the government nor the House can sack Sjahril and other members of the board of governors. \par \par \uc2  The controversy over the proposed amendments has been one of the key factors that have set back the disbursement of IMF's latest US$400 million loan tranche to Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  The other important reasons are concerns over \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  decentralization issues, and the delayed divestment of two nationalized banks. \par \par \uc2  Rizal said that it was the government that asked the House to delay the amendment process. \par \par \uc2  "We need ample time to allow for a comprehensive review by the panel of experts," he explained. \par \par \uc2  Members of the panel include two former \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  governors from Indonesia and two from Chile and New Zealand. \par \par \uc2  "As for the Indonesian experts, we will announce their names in due time," he said. \par \par \uc2  The establishment of the expert panel followed Rizal's meeting with IMF First Deputy Managing Director Stanley Fischer last month. \par \par \uc2  Separately, assistant to the Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Dipo Alam dismissed suggestions that the postponement of the debates was solely aimed at seeking the panel's recommendations. \par \par \uc2  He said that there was simply not enough time to finalize deliberations on several articles of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  law before April. \par \par \uc2  "We won't be able to complete discussions before April, even if we go ahead now; so we might as well as postpone it," Dipo told The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2  He said discussions were still deadlocked on several articles of the proposed \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  law. \par \par \uc2  Dipo added he had asked the IMF not to link the amendment of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  law with the Fund's loan disbursement. \par \par \uc2  According to him, further delay of the disbursement of the third tranche of the loan would hinder Indonesia's recovery, and would ultimately hurt the IMF's own interests. \par \par \uc2  Although the government has claimed that almost all reform targets have been completed, the IMF has yet to announce when it would send a team to Indonesia to review the next reform package to be stipulated in the new letter of intent. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the team's arrival has been further eroding international confidence in Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The Paris Club, a group of Indonesia's main foreign sovereign creditors, said earlier it may cancel new debt rescheduling talks if the country fails to reach an agreement with the IMF soon. (bkm) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx3f0035h\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
