\par\par \b \uc2  Political woes continue to plague rupiah. \b0\par\par\uc2 939 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 March 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The rupiah is likely to continue to stay at the Rp 10,000 level against the U.S. dollar this week due to the lack of fresh incentives that could lift the market sentiment, analysts have forecast. \par \par \uc2  Currency analysts and dealers share the same view that the growing concerns over the country's political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  woes would continue to undermine the Indonesian currency. \par \par \uc2  Farial Anwar, a currency analyst at a local securities company said that with the current political instability, it would be difficult for the rupiah to return to its Rp 9,000 level. \par \par \uc2  "It's very difficult now to predict the rupiah's movement," he told The Jakarta Post on Saturday. \par \par \uc2  But he was optimistic that although the situation remained unfavorable, the rupiah would continue to maintain last week's position at a range of between Rp 10,300 and Rp 10,500 against the American greenback. \par \par \uc2  The joint intervention scheme developed by \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the government will prevent the currency from breaching the Rp 11,000 level again. \par \par \uc2  On Monday, the rupiah briefly touched 11,500 after a senior \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  official remarked that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  lacked in foreign exchange capital to effectively intervene in the market. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  responded by selling dollars, and upping the rate of its overnight promissory notes by 50 basis points to push back the rupiah to 10,000. \par \par \uc2  Upon the government's request, state firms joined the fray to save the rupiah by releasing their dollar \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  However, Farial said that last week's concerted efforts by \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the government failed to bring back the rupiah to below the 10,000 level. \par \par \uc2  "Whenever the dollar got to the 9,000 level, corporations immediately stepped in to buy," he said. \par \par \uc2  According to him, the market already knows that \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  is at a critical level. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he said, was now the main dollar supplier, coming largely from the exports of crude oil and loans from international institutions. \par \par \uc2  Yet dollar demand for serving foreign debts and importing raw material alone might reach around US$50 billion this year, he said. \par \par \uc2  "And that doesn't include dollars for speculation," he added. \par \par \uc2  With gross foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  of only $29 billion, he said, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's intervention capacity was highly questionable. \par \par \uc2  Adding pressure to the meager foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 , is the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  of a $400 million loan package from the International Monetary Fund (IMF). \par \par \uc2  "The market is not hoping for the IMF's dollars ... but the IMF has become a benchmark for gaining support from other foreign donors," Farial went on saying. \par \par \uc2  The IMF has delayed its loan package since last December after Indonesia lagged in implementing key \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms targets. \par \par \uc2  Farial said that as other foreign donors had linked their loans to Indonesia complying to the IMF's reforms target, the inflow of the fresh loans was \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  He also suspected that the IMF's reluctance to disburse the loan had more to do with the agency's concerns over the government's immediate future rather than with achieving any reforms targets. \par \par \uc2  "It's not safe to channel the loans now if the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  starts having doubts over the current government's legitimacy," he explained. \par \par \uc2  The IMF would never admit tying its loans with politics, he said, but the Fund can't risk handing out $400 million to a government about to fall. \par \par \uc2  "Diplomatically it's unwise to say that your government is not credible anymore, so they (IMF) just keep picking on the LoI (Letter of Intent)," he said in reference to the LoI, which outlines the reforms targets. \par \par \uc2  When asked whether the market was trading on that worry, he answered: "Look at the facts, watch the rupiah getting weaker." \par \par \uc2  The rupiah did lose ground last week, closing Friday on 10,325 against the greenback from its previous week's closing at 10,090. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, economist Dradjad Wibowo remained upbeat on Indonesia's relation with the IMF. \par \par \uc2  "The Fund should be committed to channel its loans no matter who the president is," he said. \par \par \uc2  Yet he noted that the rupiah breached the 10,000 level, after a statement by a senior government official that an IMF review team was due to come that week, failed to materialized. \par \par \uc2  Dradjad said that the rupiah's recovery now partly hinges on certainty over the arrival of the IMF's review team; unless, he added, the government can dispel the political fog over this country, which was unlikely in the near term. \par \par \uc2  President Abdurrahman Wahid's grip on power was marked last week by the dismissal of a minister from the opposition party. \par \par \uc2  The embattled President fired Minister of Forestry Nurmahmudi Ismail, whose party is a part of Abdurrahman's staunchest political foe, the Axis force. \par \par \uc2  The weak rupiah took its toll on the stock market, with the Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX) composite index dropping to below 400, which many believed had been the market's resistance level. \par \par \uc2  Head of research at PT Ciptadana Securities, Eddy Widjoyo said fears of companies suffering from more foreign exchange losses triggered across the board selling. \par \par \uc2  Massive selling landed the JSX index at its lowest level in two years, ending the week at 380.51 from its opening at 414.10. \par \par \uc2  "Those with no positions yet, maintain a wait-and-see stance, while those with positions were cutting their losses," Eddy said. \par \par \uc2  For this week, he estimated the rupiah's woes to still drag down the JSX composite index and leave it hovering at 375. (bkm) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx3j003kg\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Panic selling pressures BI-40. \b0\par\par\uc2 317 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 March 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA: Panic selling again pressured blue chip \par \par \uc2  indices at the Jakarta Stock Exchange as investors \par \par \uc2  were troubled by internal political and external \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  factors. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, rupiah weakened again to Rp10,433 per US \par \par \uc2  dollar on discontinuation of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's market \par \par \uc2  intervention. \par \par \uc2  JSX investors were also troubled by such external \par \par \uc2  factors as worries on the Wall Street over \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  over plans to slice the Fed \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . a Fed \par \par \uc2  board meeting is scheduled to take place today (March \par \par \uc2  20). \par \par \uc2  Global investors expected the Fed to cut \b \highlight22\uc2 interest \b0 \highlight\par \par \b \highlight22\uc2  rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  by a further 50-75 basis points to reinvigorate \par \par \uc2  global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  But this may remain a dream as the latest US \par \par \uc2  statistics show that the US \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was recovering \par \par \uc2  pretty well and there would be no need to trim the Fed \par \par \uc2  rates any further for now. The Fed is likely to retain \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  at 5.4%. \par \par \uc2  Consequently the Dow Jones Index dropped below 1.900 \par \par \uc2  sending out negative sentiments across Asia and \par \par \uc2  Europe. \par \par \uc2  In Jakarta, investors went on a profit-taking spree \par \par \uc2  pulling the JSX Composite Index down by 3.51% or \par \par \uc2  13.373 points to close at 367.142 after 684.338 \par \par \uc2  million shares had changed hands on the regular board \par \par \uc2  worth Rp 254.966 billion. \par \par \uc2  The LQ-45 Index, meanwhile, dropped 4.05% to close at \par \par \uc2  71.621 while the BI-40 closed the day down 4.29% at \par \par \uc2  81.628. \par \par \uc2  Of the 40 BI-selected stocks, 31 registered losses, \par \par \uc2  only two made gains and the rest were stagnant. \par \par \uc2  Telkom made the biggest worth of transactions of Rp \par \par \uc2  60.55 billion in spite of a per-share price drop to \par \par \uc2  Rp2,325 from Rp2,475. Astra International booked Rp \par \par \uc2  35.579 billion dropping to Rp1,365 per share from \par \par \uc2  Rp1,425, HM Sampoerna made Rp 15.049 billion losing \par \par \uc2  Rp 500 per-share worth to Rp 10,850. \par \par \uc2  * Sigma Research Institute. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010710dx3k000co\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  ADB - The anxiety exaggerated. \b0\par\par\uc2 327 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 March 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The Asian Development Bank denoted that worries \par \par \uc2  about the emergence of new crisis in Asia are too exaggerated, whereas \par \par \uc2  Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery stands on strong fundamental, though have to \par \par \uc2  face tough problems. \par \par \uc2  ADB's report headlined Asia Recovery Report 2001 published yesterday \par \par \uc2  revealed the improving quality of Asian nations \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  "There is increasing endurance of the nations attacked by crisis. They are \par \par \uc2  in better position to absorb external shocks," revealed Manila based ADB. \par \par \uc2  However the institution having commitment to lend Indonesia AU$600 million \par \par \uc2  up to US$1.2 billion per year stated that the continuing political \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  caused decreasing investor crufidence. "The matter can evoke \par \par \uc2  deviating \b \highlight22\uc2 economic policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," said ADB. \par \par \uc2  The report mentioned Asian \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery in the most stricken by 1997 \par \par \uc2  crisis-Indonesia, Korea, Malaysia-will slower this year. The report is a \par \par \uc2  revision from October 2000 survey result. \par \par \uc2  Those five nations noted an average of 7.1% \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in 2000, upped \par \par \uc2  from 6.9% in 1999. The growth rate in the nations is likely to drop to 4% \par \par \uc2  this year, ADB explained. \par \par \uc2  "but situation is expected to improve in 2002, where the crisis-stricken \par \par \uc2  nations will have an average of 5% growth." \par \par \uc2  The Manila based regional development bank wrote regional external risks \par \par \uc2  peak in consequence of the slump of the US and world and the drop of \par \par \uc2  electronics demand. \par \par \uc2  According to ADB, Indonesian and Thailand \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth will down by \par \par \uc2  0.6%-1.6%, Malaysia is likely to down by 2.4%-2.9%, South Korea 1.5%-2.2%, \par \par \uc2  and the Philippine 0.9%-1.6%. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, economist Sri Mulyani Indrawati predicted that CGI's loan \par \par \uc2  commitment for APBN 2002 would decrease half from last year's amount in \par \par \uc2  consequence of the commitment drop from the majority of creditors. \par \par \uc2  "Probably it downs because ADB has stated its commitment to cut up to \par \par \uc2  half, the World Bank by one third as well as Japan," he said.(01/ab). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010710dx3k000cq\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
