\par\par \b \uc2  Consumer index retreats after slight gains. \b0\par\par\uc2 325 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 March 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Danareksa's Consumer Confidence Index in retreated to 101 in February from 103.3 in January giving up most of its gains eked out in the last couple of months as a result of falls in the present situation and expectations indices. \par \par \uc2  The Danareksa Research Institute said on Monday that the index measuring the people's assessment of the present \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation fell slightly to 82.5 from 83.0, suggesting that the earlier gain was a knee-jerk reaction to a boost in cash flows in January. \par \par \uc2  The index that measures people's expectations on their own \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  position over the next six months dropped 3.1 percent on soaring \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over where the country is heading, the institute said. \par \par \uc2  It said that the people were also more \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  about the present situation partly due to the deterioration in the labor market, with jobs becoming more difficult to find. \par \par \uc2  With security threats at the forefront of their expectations, respondents anticipated a grim outlook for the overall \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the institute said. \par \par \uc2  "Consumers are less confident in their family income expectations and this prompts them to save more of their current income as part of a contingency buffer," it added. \par \par \uc2  As nobody is able to build a lucid and reliable picture of what the future of the country, consumers are left with little choice to minimize the consequences of the possible worsening of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . This situation has also forced them to reduce their \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  on durable goods. \par \par \uc2  The institute said the proportion of the consumers' \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  for durables surveyed during the last six months dropped from 33.7 percent in January to 32.13 percent in February. \par \par \uc2  As politicians' risky behavior continues to snowball, with force and violence becoming a normal way to resolve conflicts, consumers opt to shun risks from heightening political temperatures by getting financially prepared for safety reasons.(05) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx3k003q1\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Mining stocks still under pressure. \b0\par\par\uc2 287 \uc2 words\par \uc2 21 March 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA: Mining securities on Jakarta Stock Exchange have come under another week of selling pressure due to \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political factors. \par \par \uc2  Of the six stocks under this sector none made any gain over the past week; they even registered an average loss of 6.46% as the sector's index dropped 3.11% closing at 62.512 on March 16, down from 64.519 registered on March 9. \par \par \uc2  during the period the total volume of transactions only reached 26.4 million shares worth R[23.62 billion. \par \par \uc2  Medco was the only gainer booking a 3.13% increase in per-share price to Rp825 while five other stocks such as Aneka Tambang lost 8.57%, INCO weakened by 7.19%, Tambang Timah was down 5.97%, Citatah 7.89% and Alter Abadi lost 14.29%. \par \par \uc2  Medco was favored for positive news about it over the past few months. Many investors hope that following its 1999 debt restructuring it will now expand business ion the years ahead. \par \par \uc2  Medco plans to explore 20 more oil wells this year representing a 100% increase of its expansion 