\par\par \b \uc2  IBRA selling its dollars to help stabilize rupiah. \b0\par\par\uc2 665 \uc2 words\par \uc2 23 March 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA) has started converting its dollars into rupiah in a bid to help stabilize the beleaguered local currency. \par \par \uc2  Minister of Finance Prijadi Praptosuhardjo said on Thursday that the agency sold around US$17 million last week. \par \par \uc2  Asked whether IBRA would sell more dollars in the immediate future, Prijadi said that the agency was still awaiting "clearance" from the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  regarding a recent transaction with Malaysia's Kumpulan Guthrie Bhd., which is expected to fetch around $368 million. \par \par \uc2  "IBRA will sell its dollars gradually ... But it will also depend on (rupiah) market conditions," he told reporters on the sidelines of a meeting with the House state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  committee. \par \par \uc2  He declined to provide specific details on the market conditions that would be conducive for IBRA to conduct a further dollar selloff. \par \par \uc2  IBRA is a unit under the ministry of finance, controlling billions of dollars worth of various assets transferred from recapitalized and closed banks, and former bank owners. The agency is mandated to divest the assets and raise cash to help finance the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  IBRA is believed to control around $500 million from the sale of assets, including the proceeds from the recent Guthrie transaction. \par \par \uc2  In that deal, the agency sold some 25 palm oil plantations to Guthrie in January. The sale, however, became the subject of widespread protests, which included criticism from legislators. \par \par \uc2  "The transaction is already final, but we're still waiting for further clearance from the legislature," Prijadi said, adding that IBRA was expected to submit a full report about the transaction to legislators in the near future. \par \par \uc2  Prijadi, however, said that the conversion of IBRA's dollars was not primarily aimed at propping up the embattled rupiah, which dropped to a 30-month low of Rp 11,500 per U.S. dollar earlier this month. \par \par \uc2  "It (the rupiah's plunge) is not only due to the (dollar) supply and demand factor, but other non-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  factors including social and political conditions," he said. \par \par \uc2  "Even though we can supply the market with ample dollars, it will be ineffective if (political) \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  persists. So, we'll see how effective it will be," he added. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah ended higher late on Thursday at Rp 10,390 per dollar, compared to Rp 10,425 on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  Dealers said that the lift in the local unit was supported by a concerted dollar selling campaign by \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  amid lower dollar demand from the corporate sector. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  senior deputy governor Anwar Nasution said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  would continue its intervention measures, including the sale of its dollar \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  to help stabilize the rupiah, despite declining foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has reported that the forex \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  fell to $28.57 billion as of the second week of March, down from $29.12 billion in the previous week. The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  explained that this was partly due to the repayment of government overseas debt. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  had also allowed the benchmark interest rate of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  one-month SBI promissory notes to increase to 15.24 percent on Wednesday from 14.94 percent in the previous week. \par \par \uc2  But Anwar added that \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's various measures to help boost the rupiah would be futile if security problems at home persisted and the implementation of key \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform programs progressed slowly. \par \par \uc2  As an example, he pointed out that the security problem in Aceh, which had prompted U.S. oil and gas giant ExxonMobil to temporarily halt its operations, could cause a serious blow to the overall \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  He also said that the slow progress in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform programs, such as privatization of state-owned enterprises and the sale of IBRA assets, would affect state revenue. \par \par \uc2  "These kinds of problems are far more crucial to be resolved compared to the measures that can be taken by \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  in assisting the rupiah," Anwar said.(rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx3n004ab\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
