s head of state. "There is an offer of separating the head of state from the head of government, but don't let us do that only for the sake of short-term interests by victimizing our constitution," Pramono said. On this matter, President Wahid, who is struggling to survive politically, also rejected such a compromise because it violated the 1945 Constitution. "I will not compromise on fundamental matters such as those stipulated in the constitution," he told journalists at the State Palace on Monday. The PDIP's executive board meeting mainly focused on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  affairs, including the issues of the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and soaring fuel prices. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010709dx43001kb\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
