\par\par \b \uc2  President asked to be more frugal. \b0\par\par\uc2 738 \uc2 words\par \uc2 4 April 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Finance minister Prijadi Praptosuhardjo has asked President Abdurrahman Wahid to be more frugal, including curtailing his penchant for overseas trips amid signs of a greater-than-expected \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the 2001 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "I said (to the President), 'Pak, right now I'm monitoring the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . This (the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) position could worsen.' So, I asked the President to be thrifty," Prijadi told reporters on Tuesday following a meeting with Abdurrahman at Merdeka Palace. \par \par \uc2  "Then the President replied, 'Yes, yes. I'm sorry. Well, let's start to economize, then'," Prijadi was quoted as saying by Antara. \par \par \uc2  When asked whether he had also suggested that the President avoid making overseas trips, he said that if an overseas trip was necessary it could go ahead, but it should be well-planned in order to reduce costs. \par \par \uc2  Since assuming office in October 1999, Abdurrahman, the country's first democratically-elected president, has made frequent overseas trips. He has argued that the trips were important for drumming up international support for troubled Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  But his critics have lambasted the President for leaving the country at crucial moments and pointed out that he would be better off focusing on trying to resolve the various domestic problems facing the country, including widespread social unrest and outbreaks of deadly violence. \par \par \uc2  Abdurrahman had earlier canceled a trip to Australia scheduled to begin on Tuesday. \par \par \uc2  Prijadi had earlier told the media that the 2001 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  could suffer a greater-than-expected \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  amid signs that the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  targets could be missed, as well as the delay in the full implementation of the planned fuel price increase. \par \par \uc2  A significantly larger \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  could trigger a second \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis in the ailing country. \par \par \uc2  The 2001 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  projects a \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  of around 3.7 percent of gross domestic product. \par \par \uc2  But, Prijadi said that the current weakening of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar and rising \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  could force the government to revise the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The rupiah dropped to a 30-month low of around Rp 11,500 per dollar last month amid domestic political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and a standoff between the government and the International Monetary Fund. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah ended trading late on Tuesday at Rp 10,450 per dollar, compared to the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumption of Rp 7,800 per dollar. \par \par \uc2  The weakening of the local unit has prompted \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  to allow the benchmark interest rate on one-month SBI promissory notes to rise to around 15.58 percent last week, compared to the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumption of 11 percent. \par \par \uc2  Prijadi has said that a 1 percent increase in the SBI rate could cause an increase of around Rp 2.1 trillion in the interest cost of the government's bank recapitalization bonds. \par \par \uc2  The government has issued around Rp 430 trillion worth of bonds to help finance the massive bank recapitalization program. The \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  makes provision for the interest on the bonds. \par \par \uc2  Prijadi also said that the delay in the full implementation of the fuel price hike plan would put further pressure on the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The government initially planned to increase fuel prices in April in a bid to reduce the government \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  for the commodity. But, as a result of the current political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the government has only raised the fuel price for industrial users to between 50 percent and 100 percent of the market price,. The fuel price for small companies, the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the state electricity utility and the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  transportation sector remains unchanged. \par \par \uc2  Prijadi confirmed on Tuesday that his office was sounding out measures to raise domestic revenues and cut \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  so as to relieve the pressure on the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Asked about plans to seek new foreign loans at an upcoming key donors' meeting in Jakarta, Prijadi said that the meeting would basically review the country's performance as regards the achievement of key \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform targets over the past six months. \par \par \uc2  He said that it was still not definite that the government would ask for new loan commitments. \par \par \uc2  The country's donors are grouped in the Consultative Group on Indonesia (CGI). \par \par \uc2  Pre-CGI meetings will be held on April 23 and April 24, to be followed by a full CGI meeting in October or November of this year. \par \par \uc2  At the last CGI meeting in Tokyo, the donors pledged around US$5.2 billion in loans to Indonesia. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Documen