\par\par \b \uc2  Black market aggravating crisis, ex-minister warns. \b0\par\par\uc2 587 \uc2 words\par \uc2 14 April 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  2 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Black market activities over the past three years have contributed to the worsening of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis, former manpower minister Bomer Pasaribu said. \par \par \uc2  Bomer urged all parties to pay serious attention as the black market has grown robustly over the last three years. \par \par \uc2  He contended that awareness toward black market activities should be given equal priority as the focus on improving \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals, for the effects were almost equally as debilitating. \par \par \uc2  "Corruption, smuggling, illegal logging, narcotics and trade in bogus academic titles are just five of 12 illegal activities which are growing robustly in the reform era," he said here on Thursday. \par \par \uc2  The other seven were collusive and nepotistic practices, piracy in Indonesian waters, prostitution, the distribution of pornographic CDs and VCDs, bribery of the judiciary, money politics and gambling. \par \par \uc2  Bomer, also chairman of the Center for Labor and Development Studies (CLDS), said besides paying no \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 , these illicit businesses had affected the labor market and employment. \par \par \uc2  He said further that based on secondary data collected by CLDS, the prevalent black market was related to the continuing legal and political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , ineffective state institutions, especially the government and the legislature, and security instability. \par \par \uc2  "The black market during the New Order era reached only around 4 percent (of domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity) because strict law and order were maintained," he said, while estimating that currently the black market accounts for over one-third of domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity. \par \par \uc2  Bomer pointed out that the absence of stiff legal sanctions against corruptors had contributed to the rise of corruption to alarming levels. \par \par \uc2  "It isn't unexpected that several international institutions have ranked Indonesia second on the list of the most corrupt countries in the world," he said. \par \par \uc2  Bomer quipped that the government should build more prisons before applying a reversal of the burden of proof within the legal system. \par \par \uc2  "If the new investigation system is enforced, half of the law enforcers could be jailed because of their alleged involvement." \par \par \uc2  Bomer further noted that according to data from the forestry and marine resources ministries, the government lost US$8.9 billion due to illegal logging and $12 billion from illegal fishing in 1999. \par \par \uc2  He further charged that Indonesia was now ranked fourth in the list of narcotics supplier countries in Asia and 10th in the world. \par \par \uc2  "We can imagine the debilitating impact of the narcotics trade within the country over the next three decades if our younger generation consumes narcotics," he said. \par \par \uc2  He warned that Indonesia might be on the verge of losing a generation due to a combination of a weak education system caused by conflicts in numerous regions, the large number of refugees and the narcotics trade. \par \par \uc2  On the trade in phony academic titles, Bomer remarked that a doctorate could easily be obtained at a cost of between Rp 10 million to Rp 15 million. \par \par \uc2  "Numerous local and international educational institutions that have no official permit from the government are intensively offering various academic titles through media advertisements," he said. \par \par \uc2  There is an allegation that the practice has become so prolific that recently an academic institution also offered a fast-track PhD to Vice President Megawati Soekarnoputri and Tresna Dermawan, chairman of the supervisory board of private universities in West Java. \par \par \uc2  Ronny R. Nitibhaskara, chairman of the supervisory board of private universities in Jakarta, conceded recently that numerous educational institutions had offered business management diplomas, masters and PhD programs without official permits from the relevant authorities. (rms) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx4e004jd\par }\page {\par\fs20\b  \highlight22\uc2 Deficit \highlight\uc2  to affect macroeconomic stability. \b0\par\par\uc2 294 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 April 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The government's efforts to cover the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  will \par \par \uc2  not be effective if not carried out with efforts to maintain macroeconomic \par \par \uc2  stability, an observer had said. \par \par \uc2  "Financing from privatization or from IBRA asset sales is only one \par \par \uc2  alternative. The key is macroeconomic stability," economist Sri Adiningsih \par \par \uc2  said on the sideline of a discussion yesterday. \par \par \uc2  According to her, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  deterioration occurred due to inability to \par \par \uc2  maintain macroeconomic stability and that it is not always caused by \par \par \uc2  non-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  factors like politics. The current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development is \par \par \uc2  showing vivid deterioration. \par \par \uc2  The indication is reflected in the increasing intensity in terms of foreign \par \par \uc2  exchange money market indicator, stock exchange and bearish real sector. \par \par \uc2  The \par \par \b \hi