2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The government are asked not to increase and \par \par \uc2  broaden \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  basics to cover up \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  because the move will weaken \par \par \uc2  purchasing power of society. \par \par \uc2  The proposal is one of political items agreed as recommendation at the end \par \par \uc2  of the national conference of National Mandate Party (PAN) in Bali, signed \par \par \uc2  by chief head Amien Rais and secretary general M.Hatta Radjasa. \par \par \uc2  The recommendation stipulates that \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  problem is the result of \par \par \uc2  the weakening of rupiah and increase of interest rate. \par \par \uc2  According to PAN, \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  can only be overcome by proper \par \par \uc2  macroeconomic management \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and consistency accompanied by political \par \par \uc2  and security stability recovery. \par \par \uc2  "The government should avoid the short way to cover up \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  by \par \par \uc2  increasing and broadening \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  resources excessively," the recommendation \par \par \uc2  says. \par \par \uc2  PAN suggests to government to be selectively thrifty to \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and state \par \par \uc2  owned company privatisation, selling out of IBRA's assets and avoid \par \par \uc2  conflicts with International Monetary Fund and donor agencies, including \par \par \uc2  protecting assets belonging to domestic and foreign investors. \par \par \uc2  PAN evaluates that investment stagnation and export decreases are the \par \par \uc2  result of \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  weakness and political and law \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Therefore, the recommendation continues, the government need to quickly \par \par \uc2  take up the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of safety and relief in form of financial incentive and \par \par \uc2  laxity. \par \par \uc2  Amin Rais, upon closing the meeting asserted that \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problems are \par \par \uc2  not actually mere fundamentals factor but are inflicted more by distrust \par \par \uc2  of investors and donors agencies sides toward the government. (dw). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010710dx4j000ja\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Kadin - Capital Flights Are Still Taking Place. \b0\par\par\uc2 470 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 April 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The rupiah flowing abroad (capital flights) are \par \par \uc2  difficult to stop because of the worsening domestic political and security \par \par \uc2  condition, Aburizal Bakrie, president of Indonesian trade and industry \par \par \uc2  association (Kadin) yesterday. \par \par \uc2  According to Aburizal, rupiah flowing abroad is hardly to come back if \par \par \uc2  there is not law, political and security certainty in Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  "It is proper to know that funds parked overseas are growing because \par \par \uc2  investors are worried to invest in Indonesia, which is an unsafe place for \par \par \uc2  them," he said after attending the third regional conference of Middle \par \par \uc2  Java Kadin in Semarang yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Bakrie said money does not know nationalism and will move away in search \par \par \uc2  of safer and more profitable investments. "Money are the biggest coward \par \par \uc2  and does not know nationalism at all," he asserted. \par \par \uc2  He cited an example, if the money was insecure, the money had already run \par \par \uc2  before the owner. On the contrary, if the conditions are secure the money \par \par \uc2  owners do no