erted. \par \par \uc2  According to him, how many times Indonesian government changes, it will \par \par \uc2  not have grave impacts as long as there is not the change in \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  He said that there is separation between politics and \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , but the \par \par \uc2  fact is that \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth is slowing down not because of political \par \par \uc2  factors. \par \par \uc2  Bakrie explained the problem is that there is law \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , such as \par \par \uc2  cancellations of cooperation or agreements, the worsening of security, or \par \par \uc2  workers activities that burn industries, industries rampaging or \par \par \uc2  prohibition for industries to product, said Bakrie (rsj). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010710dx4j000jd\par }\page {\par\fs20\b  \highlight22\uc2 Deficit \highlight\uc2  Influeces Macroeconomic Stability. \b0\par\par\uc2 372 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 April 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The government's efforts to cover up \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  will not be effective unless accompanied by the move to maintain \par \par \uc2  macroeconomic stability, says an observer. \par \par \uc2  "The funding by privatisation or selling out IBRA's assets is only one \par \par \uc2  alternative. The basics of \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  actually derive from macroeconomic \par \par \uc2  stability," Sri Adinigsih, economist from Universitas Gajah Mada explained \par \par \uc2  on the sidelines of conference titled Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the Brink of \par \par \uc2  Collapse in Jakarta yesterday. \par \par \uc2  According to her, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slump down is inflicted by ma