\par\par \b \uc2  BI will continue to defend ailing rupiah. \b0\par\par\uc2 791 \uc2 words\par \uc2 28 April 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor Sjahril Sabirin pledged here on Friday to further defend the ailing rupiah, which has been under pressure in the past few weeks amid growing conflict among political leaders. \par \par \uc2  Sjahril said the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  would use usual measures including intervention into the currency market and raising \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to halt the rupiah's fall. \par \par \uc2  "\b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  will continue to use the two usual measures ... If we think we need to intervene, we'll do so," Sjahril told reporters at the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  office. \par \par \uc2  Sjahril made the statement amid criticism including from the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  that the market intervention and high interest rate measures have failed to stabilize the embattled rupiah, which dropped to a 31-month low of Rp 12,300 per U.S. dollar at one point on Thursday. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah gained ground on Friday to close at Rp 11,800 per dollar after several state-owned banks sold their dollars to defend the Indonesian currency. \par \par \uc2  "Don't look at the intervention as a means to eliminate the main factors causing the rupiah to weaken. The intervention is only meant to reduce the sharp fluctuation in the currency market," Sjahril said. \par \par \uc2  He explained that the current weakening of the rupiah was caused by a combination of domestic political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problems particularly the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the relations between the government and the International Monetary Fund (IMF). \par \par \uc2  The domestic political conditions have been shaken by the prospect of violence between the opponents and supporters of embattled President Abdurrahman Wahid as the House planned to issue a second memorandum of censure to the President next week, which may lead to his impeachment. \par \par \uc2  On the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  front, the government failed to reach a new agreement with visiting IMF special mission last week. The latter left the country after stating a precondition for signing a new agreement that the government must first obtain approval from the House over its proposed revision of the current 2001 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The signing of the agreement would pave the way for the disbursement of the IMF's next US$400 million loan tranche to the country which was delayed late last year. \par \par \uc2  "As long as the rupiah remains under pressure, the interest rate may continue to increase," Sjahril said. \par \par \uc2  The benchmark interest rate of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  one-month SBI promissory notes has soared to 16.09 percent, a level which analysts say could spell new trouble to domestic banks. This will also increase the government's burden in financing the interest payment of the massive bank recapitalization bonds. \par \par \uc2  But Sjahril dismissed the concern. "According to the information I received, it (the 16 percent rate) was still a safe level... If pressure on the rupiah remained, the interest rate may still rise, but let's hope it won't," he said. \par \par \uc2  Sjahril said that it was crucial for the government to reach an agreement with the IMF because it would help revive investors confidence in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and help stabilize the local currency. \par \par \uc2  "The rupiah is currently undervalued, but whether it will continue to drop will depend on market confidence. If confidence remains weak, it's impossible to see a stronger rupiah," he said. \par \par \uc2  "I think reaching an agreement with the IMF is very crucial to revive confidence and lift the rupiah," he added. \par \par \uc2  During a meeting with Finance Minister Prijadi Praptosuhardjo late on Thursday, House leaders questioned the high interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  adopted by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to help defend the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  Head of the House Commission IX on state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  Benny Pasaribu told a press conference following the meeting that the high interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  had been "too costly" to the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and so far had not been effective. \par \par \uc2  Benny said that the House demanded the government talk with \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  to design concrete measures to help strengthen the rupiah as a prerequisite for a speedy approval of the government-proposed revision of the current state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The government plans to revise the current state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  as the various assumptions it is based on are no longer realistic due to the weakening of the rupiah and soaring \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The government plans to start the debating process on the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  revision with the House early next month and expects to reach a final agreement at the end of the month. \par \par \uc2  According to a government document leaked to the press, the new assumed rupiah-dollar rate in the revised \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is set at Rp 9,600 per dollar, while the SBI rate is set at 15 percent. The current \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  sets the rupiah-dollar rate at Rp 7,800 per dollar and SBI rate at 11.5 percent. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx4s0058t\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
