\par\par \b \uc2  Small, medium scale firms survive crisis. \b0\par\par\uc2 395 \uc2 words\par \uc2 30 April 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  2 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  YOGYAKARTA (JP): Small and medium scale businesses have survived well during the prolonged monetary and banking crisis, despite the absence of financial aid from multilateral creditors, the head of Yogyakarta's Association of \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Scholars (ISEI) said here on Sunday. \par \par \uc2  Arief Ramelan Karseno told a press conference at the Yogyakarta Garuda Natour Hotel that the national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  meltdown, had even encouraged the small and medium scale businesses - run by the private sector - to find ways to grow. \par \par \uc2  "Small and medium scale enterprises have almost nothing to do with the monetary and banking crisis," he said. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  of the International Monetary Fund's (IMF) loan disbursement to the government has indirectly encouraged the small and medium enterprises to boost their exports, Karseno, lecturer at Gadjah Mada University's school of economics, said. \par \par \uc2  Also present at the press conference were senior economist Dibyo Prabowo and Mubyarto from Gadjah Mada University. \par \par \uc2  Karseno also said that the government's efforts to liberalize the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  had encouraged self-sufficiency and confidence among the small and medium scale enterprises. \par \par \uc2  "It's true that the rupiah has sunk to a low level against foreign currencies especially the U.S. dollar, but in fact the inflation rate in 2000 was only 9.3 percent because the national stock of basic goods was sufficient. This means that the real drop in the rupiah's value domestically was only 9.3 percent," he said. \par \par \uc2  He criticized other fellow economists, who often expressed pessimism and underestimated the national \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , ignoring the real people's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Karseno said that the lingering monetary crisis in the country had been engineered by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials, who wanted to undermine the government. \par \par \uc2  "History tells us that \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has always been used (by politicians) as a tool against their rivals," he said. \par \par \uc2  Large scale businesses, which had enjoyed protection under the previous regime had been the most-affected sector in the ongoing crisis. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile Mubyarto said that the small and medium scale enterprises had demonstrated their vigor during the crisis, therefore the government must make real efforts to promote them and review its plan to seek more loans. \par \par \uc2  "If we trust the strength of the people's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , I think \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery will be well on its way. New foreign loans may be unnecessary," he said. (44) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx4u0059m\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
