\par\par \b \uc2  Govt, DPR set to start  \highlight22\uc2 budget \highlight\uc2  debate. \b0\par\par\uc2 633 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 May 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The government planned to meet with the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  on Thursday to start the deliberation process of the proposed state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  revision, Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Rizal Ramli said on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  Rizal expected the deliberation process could be completed quickly despite the ongoing political rift between legislators and President Abdurrahman Wahid. \par \par \uc2  "We plan to submit the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  revision (to the House) on Thursday," he told reporters at his office. \par \par \uc2  Finance Minister Prijadi Praptosuhardjo had earlier said that the House was expected to give its approval to the revision of 2001 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  by the end of this month. \par \par \uc2  The approval is crucial to pave the way for the International Monetary Fund to disburse its next US$400 million loan tranche to the country. \par \par \uc2  The sharp drop in the exchange rate of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar and the rising domestic interest rate have forced the government to revise the current state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Under the proposed revision, the exchange rate of the rupiah would be set at Rp 9,600 per U.S. dollar (compared to the initial assumption of Rp 7,800 per dollar), inflation at 9.3 percent (compared to 7.2 percent), the interest rate of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  SBI notes at 15 percent (11.5 percent), and gross domestic product at 3.5 percent (5 percent). \par \par \uc2  The rupiah dropped to below Rp 12,000 per dollar recently amid continuing domestic political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The rupiah ended at Rp 11,160 per dollar late on Wednesday. The SBI interest rate is now at 16.16 percent, while year-on-year inflation had reached double digits over the past couple of months. \par \par \uc2  The drop in the rupiah and the rising interest rate would widen the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  to 6 percent of GDP, compared to the initial projection of 3.7 percent of GDP, unless measures were immediately taken. \par \par \uc2  The government is proposing a \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  adjustment package to try to contain the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  at the initial projection level by cutting down \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  and boosting domestic revenue. \par \par \uc2  Although some legislators have said that they would agree to expedite the deliberation of the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  revision, experts have said that the embattled government might face difficulties from legislators amid the current political fighting between the legislature and Abdurrahman. \par \par \uc2  The House earlier this week issued a second censure against Abdurrahman over two financial scandals. This may lead to the President's impeachment. \par \par \uc2  Head of the House State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  Committee Benny Pasaribu recently told reporters that the government must come up with concrete measures, particularly to stabilize the rupiah, so that the deliberation process could be completed as soon as possible. \par \par \uc2  The government has said that it would increase the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and excise revenue target this year by around Rp 3 trillion to help limit the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Director General for Customs and Excise Permana Agung said on Wednesday that the minimum retail cigarette price would be increased by an average of 10 percent starting July to raise the excise \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue target this year by around Rp 500 billion. \par \par \uc2  The government-sanctioned minimum retail price was last increased in April. \par \par \uc2  The government also plans to raise the target for proceeds from privatization this year by around Rp 2.2 trillion to reach approximately Rp 8.7 trillion, and to raise around Rp 5.2 trillion from resource-rich provinces and districts by issuing bonds, selling shares in state enterprises, and selling assets held by the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency. \par \par \uc2  As regarding \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the government plans to further cut \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and streamline development \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Rizal called on government officials to help the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  by cutting down on non-urgent \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  including funds allocated for foreign consultants in various government projects. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx53005kl\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Property stocks down in April. \b0\par\par\uc2 172 \uc2 words\par \uc2 4 May 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA: Property stocks declined 7.85% during the \par \par \uc2  month of April due to various reasons including \par \par \uc2  political and macro-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The sector only saw 752.761 million shares changing \par \par \uc2  hands worth Rp252. 843 billion. \par \par \uc2  Up to six stocks made gains, 15 came under selling \par \par \uc2  pressure and the rest were stagnant. \par \par \uc2  During April the index of this sector dropped 3.59 \par \par \uc2  points to 39.947 at the JSX Composite Index lost 4.94% \par \par \uc2  from 381.05 (March 30) to 362.22. \par \par \uc2  Internal factors in this sector were to blame for the \par \par \uc2  lack of enthusiasm. \par \par \uc2  The 50% discount on principal debts in this sector \par \par \uc2  failed to encourage investors. \par \par \uc2  The situation was made worse by rising \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  and difficulty in getting fresh bank loans. \par \par \uc2  It is still difficult to predict whether this sector \par \par \uc2  will be prolific in the long run. \par \par \uc2  Many investors thought that so long as there are \par \par \uc2  still political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , it is hard to expect \par \par \uc2  investors to grab the stocks in this sector. \par \par \uc2  * Sigma Research Institute. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010710dx54000ng\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
