\par\par \b \uc2  KPEN warns govt not to overtax businesses. \b0\par\par\uc2 709 \uc2 words\par \uc2 4 May 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The National \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Recovery Committee (KPEN) urged the government on Thursday not to burden local companies with more \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  in its efforts to reduce the widening \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the country's state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  KPEN executive Sofjan Wanandi said the higher \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  burden would inflict further pain on the country's ailing business sector. \par \par \uc2  "I'm afraid that the greatest burden from the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  revision will be faced by the business sector," Sofjan told reporters at a media meeting. \par \par \uc2  The business sector, he said, had always been an easy target for the government whenever it needed a boost in revenues. "It's like going hunting at a zoo; that's what's happening now," he added. \par \par \uc2  The sharp drop in the rupiah and continual increases in \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  in recent months have caused a widening of the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  to about 6 percent of gross domestic product or about Rp 88 trillion (about US$80 billion at the current exchange rate) from an initial target of 3.7 percent. \par \par \uc2  The government has been preparing a number of alternatives to cover the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , including a raising of the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  receipt target by Rp 3 trillion. \par \par \uc2  "Judging from the revenue assumptions the government has, I think that will be difficult to achieve," Sofjan said. This difficulty, he said, might cause the government to impose higher \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  on existing taxpayers. \par \par \uc2  "While instead, the government should seek to broaden the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  base," he added. \par \par \uc2  Former director general for \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Machfud Sidik, has said that the country depended too much on corporate \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and was slow in tapping the potential of individual taxpayers. \par \par \uc2  According to him, of approximately 20 million potential private taxpayers, only 1.3 million were registered with his office. And even then, only a handful pay their \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  in full. \par \par \uc2  "We are willing to work harder and make sacrifices only if you (the government) work harder too," Sofjan continued. \par \par \uc2  He said that although KPEN did not object to the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  revision, it wanted the revision to take into account industry's shaky recovery. \par \par \uc2  Since the 1997-98 \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis, the country's real sector has yet to fully regain its pre-crisis strength. \par \par \uc2  Blocking its path to recovery is a multitude of problems, many of which are rooted in the country's chaotic political landscape. \par \par \uc2  President Abdurrahman Wahid and legislators are locked in a drawn-out standoff that has been escalating since early this year. \par \par \uc2  Legislators' moves to initiate an impeachment process have dashed hopes of political stability returning soon. \par \par \uc2  KPEN chairman Aburizal Bakrie, who also heads the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (Kadin), said political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  hampered investment decisions. \par \par \uc2  He predicted that many companies might not make it through this year if political instability continued to hamper business activities. \par \par \uc2  The lack of new investment might also cost the country the strong export and consumption growth it had enjoyed last year, according to economists. \par \par \uc2  To maintain recovery, industries need to invest in expansion, yet funding sources are scarce, with the banking sector still unable to resume its role as lender. \par \par \uc2  Loans from banks have become expensive as \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  have soared in line with the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's move to hike its certificate rates. \par \par \uc2  Aburizal said \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  should have avoided raising its \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  in defending the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  This year alone, the rupiah has lost around 17 percent of its value, largely caused by political tensions. \par \par \uc2  To prevent the rupiah from being used to purchase the U.S dollar, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  raised its certificate rate, which now stands at over 16 percent. \par \par \uc2  "Raising \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  only causes more bleeding in the banking sector," Aburizal explained. \par \par \uc2  Banks suffer from negative spread when the revenue they get from \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  on loans falls below the interest payments they make to depositors. \par \par \uc2  He also urged \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  to soften the prudential banking requirements imposed on banks this year. \par \par \uc2  He suggested that this year's minimum capital adequacy ratio for banks be lowered from 8 percent to 6 percent. \par \par \uc2  He further proposed an easing of the requirement for the minimum non-performing loan ratio from 5 percent this year, to 5 percent over the next two years. (bkm) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost00200107