\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia \highlight\uc2  remains unmoved by inflation threat. \b0\par\par\uc2 701 \uc2 words\par \uc2 5 May 2001\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor Sjahril Sabirin said on Friday that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  would not loosen its tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , despite complaints from the government that the current interest rate level was already too high, due to concerns over the threat of inflation. \par \par \uc2  Sjahril also said that although the rupiah had recovered lately, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  would not move hastily to lower its benchmark interest rate. \par \par \uc2  "We're still concerned with inflation. We won't hastily change our \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  (on the interest rate)," he told reporters at the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  headquarters following the weekly Friday prayer. \par \par \uc2  "We still have to wait for further developments (in the rupiah and inflation)," he added. \par \par \uc2  The Central Bureau of Statistics reported on Wednesday that year-on-year inflation in April reached 10.51 percent. \par \par \uc2  The Bureau warned that inflation this year could reach a double digit level as the year-on-year inflation level during the past three months had reached around 10 percent. \par \par \uc2  The government had initially forecast inflation in 2001 to average at 7.2 percent. But the government is now planning to revise the forecast to around 9.3 percent amid deterioration in the country's macroeconomic condition. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has allowed its benchmark interest rate to continue to rise during the past several months in a bid to help defend the ailing rupiah as well as curb inflationary pressure. \par \par \uc2  The benchmark interest rate of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's one-month SBI promissory notes increased again to 16.16 percent on Wednesday at the weekly regular auction. \par \par \uc2  Analysts said that stronger inflation was primarily contributed to by the weakening of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar as the country's production system relied heavily on imported raw materials. \par \par \uc2  Last week, the rupiah plunged to a 31-month low of Rp 12,300 per dollar, compared to the government 2001 target of Rp 7,800 per dollar, amid worries over possible violence between supporters and opponents of President Abdurrahman Wahid, who was facing a second censure by the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  over alleged involvement in two financial scandals. \par \par \uc2  But as the violence did not materialize after the House issued its second censure early this week, the rupiah managed to appreciate during the past few days and reached around Rp 10,976 per dollar late on Friday. \par \par \uc2  Analysts, however, said that the risk of the rupiah falling again was still high as there were no signs of improving relations between Abdurrahman and the House. The censure could lead to the impeachment of the President by the People's Consultative Assembly, possibly in August. \par \par \uc2  "If pressure on the rupiah remains due to various \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , it's normal for us (\b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) to react (through interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 )," said Sjahril, who has been asked by Abdurrahman to resign. The government is proposing a bill to the House to amend the existing \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  law that may result in the dismissal of Sjahril. \par \par \uc2  Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Rizal Ramli had earlier complained that the current interest rate level was already too high and could be detrimental to the still weak banking sector, stalled \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, and could impose a heavier burden on the already strained state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Bankers have also warned that if the benchmark interest rate reaches the 17 percent level, many banks could suffer further financial woes. \par \par \uc2  The higher SBI rate would also increase the burden of the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which covers the interest of the massive bonds issued by the government to finance the country's bank recapitalization program. The burden will be even greater if the government has to spend more to recapitalize banks that are badly affected by the soaring interest rate. \par \par \uc2  Banks have also complained that the higher interest rate had created difficulties for them to restructure the huge non-performing loans (NPL), which according to \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's ruling must be reduced to the 5 percent level by the end of this year. \par \par \uc2  But Sjahril reaffirmed that \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  would not impose the 5 percent NPL requirement this year, although banks must still meet the year-end minimum 8 percent capital adequacy ratio or risk closure. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2001 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010712dx55000e3\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  DPR Still Waiting for State  \highlight22\uc2 Budget \highlight\uc2  2001 Revision. \b0\par\par\uc2 318 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 May 2001\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2001 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The House \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  Committee is still waiting for the \par \par \uc2  government to submit state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  200